ce:section.ce:para:
Taking cues from the previous knowledge, the present work focuses on the advancement of materiobiology in the avenue of bioimaging by studying the cumulative impact of reaction parameters (HT, RT, precursor mass (MMHA), solvent (Vwater), and EDA (VEDA) concentrations) on the synthesis of multi-color NCQDs. Herein, NCQDs act as a neoteric trident in the field of cancer biology to facilitate multi-color imaging, track in-vitro photostability, and induce migration. Inspired by the promising aspects of the statistical approach, herein grey relational analysis (GRA) was adopted to ascertain the best process parameters for the pristine fabrication of the NCQDs from Muellar Hinton agar (MHA) and EDA via hydrothermal carbonization (HTC) route (
                        Scheme 1

                     ). In support of GRA, we developed and trained a feed-forward ANN model using pre-existing input–output datasets to simulate the quality attributes when subjected to out-of-bound reaction conditions [14]. Prior to biomedical applications, the physicochemical characteristics of NCQDs were thoroughly characterized. In addition to the above, the multi-color cell imaging capabilities of NCQDs were also explored under in-vitro/vivo conditions. Finally, the histological and cytotoxic assays were examined to validate the holistic biocompatible proficiency of the biogenic NCQDs in-vitro/vivo. We hypothesized that the brilliance of AI over materiobiology would serve as a versatile platform for simultaneous medical diagnosis and high-efficacy therapy. Moreover, a general but elusive goal is to ensure the biomedical safety of nanoprobes, establishing them as a safe platform for tumor therapy and multimodal imaging in-vivo.

The monodispersed NCQDs with various sizes were fabricated via a simple and universal HTC route ( Scheme 1 ) with slight modifications [18]. Herein, MHA served as a primary carbon source, while EDA, a nitrogenous base, functioned both as a catalyst for the intra/inter molecular dehydration of MHA and as an N-dopant [19]. Furthermore, distilled water was selected as a potential solvent during the HTC process. The comprehensive protocol illustrating the pristine synthesis of NCQDs is described in the Supporting Information file. Empirically, five parameters (HT, RT, MMHA, Vwater, and VEDA) and their corresponding levels ( Table 1
) were designated as input process parameters for the HTC process. Based on input parameters and their respective values, an L16 orthogonal array (OA) was executed using Minitab17® software to determine optimum conditions for the pristine synthesis of NCQDs. Here, each experimental condition was repeated thrice (n = 3) to enhance the reproducibility of the synthesis route. According to the L16 OA combinations, NCQDs were synthesized, and the quality attributes such as QY, conductivity (CO), and polydispersity index (PDI) were evaluated, and their average values are summarized in Table 2
. Later, the GRA technique was utilized to formulate the grey relational grades (GRG) for all possible combinations. The detailed procedures for executing the GRA approach are illustrated in the Supporting Information file (
Table S1-S4
), and the computed GRG is displayed in Table 2 .

Henceforth, the developed model can further be recommended for predicting the performance of NCQDs under out-of-bound reaction conditions (which is not listed in 
                           Table 2
                        ). So as to confirm the effectiveness of the model in out-of-bound parametric situations, the NCQDs’ performances under condition OE were also anticipated through the feed-forward ANN model and compared with the experimental one (as summarized in 
                           Table 5

                        ). The response characteristics forecasted by the ANN architecture under the OE (
                           Table 5
                        ) condition align well with those attained from the confirmation test (
                           Table 3
                        ). This finding demonstrates the developed ANN network’s reliability and accuracy and further directs the model for predicting the NCQDs characteristics for out-of-bound parametric combinations.

Moreover, the impact of different hydrothermal parameters (HT, RT, MMHA, VWater, and VEDA) upon NCQDs quality attributes (QY, PDI, and CO) was statistically evaluated using analysis of variance (ANOVA). ANOVA analysis was conducted using Minitab-17® software. The detailed ANOVA analysis is reported in the Supporting Information file (
Table S6
). It also discerns the prime HTC parameter and its percentage (%) influence toward a distinct feature of NCQDs ( Fig. S1
).

The photostability of the water-soluble NCQDs was monitored under a high-energy 365 nm UV lamp. As shown in Fig. S7
(d), the NCQDs demonstrated excellent photostability after continuous UV irradiation for 60 min. This outstanding photostability can be ascribed to the presence of electronegative functional groups on their surface [48,71]. Furthermore, the photostability of the OE sample was compared with that of Fluorescein isothiocyanate (FITC; an organic fluorophore) using CLSM at their respective excitation wavelengths (λOE=405 nm and λFITC=488 nm). The OE sample ( Fig. S8
) exhibited extreme photostability, with insignificant change in FL intensity observed after 60 min irradiation. On the contrary, the FL of FITC ( Fig. S9 ) was bleached by 53 % after 10 min of laser exposure.
